---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const updated = 'July 23, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Wu Xing Wellness"
  description="How Wu Xing Wellness handles your information, cookies, advertising and affiliate links."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--ink-faint);font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        Wu Xing Wellness ("we", "us") publishes educational content about traditional Chinese wellness at
        fiveelementsbalance.com. This policy explains what information we collect and how it is used. We do not
        practice medicine and we never ask you to share personal health information.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Information you give us:</strong> If you email us, we receive the email address and content you choose to send. We use it only to reply and do not add you to any list.</li>
        <li><strong>Automatic data:</strong> Like most websites, our hosting and analytics tools may log standard technical data (browser type, pages visited, referring site, approximate region). This is aggregated and not linked to your name.</li>
        <li><strong>We do not collect personal health information.</strong> Our quizzes run entirely in your browser and are not stored on our servers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies for advertising and basic site function. See our
        <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a> for details and how to control them.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising — Google AdSense</h2>
      <p>
        We may display ads via Google AdSense. Google and its partners use cookies to serve ads based on your
        prior visits to this and other websites. You can opt out of personalised advertising at
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>,
        and learn more from
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's advertising policies</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Some links on this site are affiliate links, primarily Amazon Associates. If you click one and make a
        purchase, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. We only link to products we believe are
        relevant to the topic. As an Amazon Associate we earn from qualifying purchases.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party content</h2>
      <p>
        Embedded content (such as videos or ads) from third parties may set its own cookies. We do not control
        these and recommend reviewing their privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>This site is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from them.</p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>US — CCPA:</strong> California residents may request access to or deletion of personal information we hold about them.</li>
        <li><strong>EU/UK — GDPR:</strong> You have rights to access, correct, or delete your data, and to object to processing.</li>
        <li>To exercise any right, email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time; the "last updated" date above reflects the latest revision.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about privacy? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
